stylometry: Goal Seek is used to alter decision variables in order to obtain a desired outcome. A data table, also known as a what -if analysis, has two types a one-way data table and a two way data table. In a one way data table, one input is used and several outputs can be the result over a given range. In a two-way data table, 2 inputs are used to determine one specific output. These could be used in a model in determining which investment to make. For example, I have decided that I want to invest $5,000 that I have saved. I go to a financial advisor and he suggests two options that he thinks will work for me. I would use a what-if analysis to determine how much of a return I would receive with each investment over different time periods. I could also use goal seek and have the different levels of time (1 yr, 5 yr, 10yr) which would be my decision variables to find out which investment to use in order to obtain a desired return. I therefore could alter my decision variables in order to acheive an objective.
